---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Hamilton Jazzmaster: American Soul, Swiss Heart" description="The Hamilton American Classic Jazzmaster H32505731 reimagines mid-century American design with Swiss precision. A story of rhythm and time.">
  <article class="story-article">
    <header class="story-header">
      <div class="story-category">Design & Heritage</div>
      <h1>Hamilton Jazzmaster:<br>American Soul, Swiss Heart</h1>
      <div class="story-meta-line">
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>Hamilton</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="story-hero-img">
      <img src="https://cdnstatic.creationwatches.com/products/product-images/l/H32505731_LRG.webp" alt="Hamilton Jazzmaster H32505731" />
    </div>

    <div class="story-body">
      <p class="story-lede">
        Jazz is music made from imperfections. The off-beat, the blue note, the unexpected silence. It's a fitting name for a watch that takes the classic dress watch formula and adds just enough character to make it sing.
      </p>

      <h2>Mid-Century Reimagined</h2>
      <p>
        The Hamilton Jazzmaster line debuted in the early 2000s as a tribute to the American watches of the 1950s and 60s — a golden era when Hamilton was the undisputed king of American watchmaking. The <strong>H32505731</strong> captures that spirit with a clean, silver dial, polished dauphine hands, and thin applied indices. It looks like it belongs in a smoke-filled jazz club, catching the glow of amber lights.
      </p>
      <p>
        At 40mm, the case is perfectly proportioned for modern wrists while maintaining the elegance of vintage proportions. The polished bezel catches light, and the gently curved lugs ensure it hugs the wrist. The crown at 3 o'clock is signed with Hamilton's H logo — a small touch that signals attention to detail.
      </p>

      <h2>A Movement That Swings</h2>
      <p>
        Inside ticks the H-10 automatic movement — Hamilton's in-house caliber based on the ETA C07.111. What makes it special isn't complexity; it's endurance. With an 80-hour power reserve, you can set it down on Friday evening and pick it up Monday morning without resetting the time. For a dress watch that you might rotate with other pieces, this is transformative.
      </p>
      <p>
        The movement beats at 21,600 vibrations per hour — a relaxed pace that reduces wear and extends service intervals. Through the sapphire exhibition caseback, you can watch the decorated movement at work, the rotor spinning with each movement of your wrist.
      </p>

      <h2>Versatility in Simplicity</h2>
      <p>
        The Jazzmaster earns its keep through versatility. On its black leather strap with deployant buckle, it dresses up effortlessly. Navy suit? Perfect. Charcoal blazer? Even better. But unlike many dress watches that look out of place with jeans, the H32505731 dials down its formality just enough to work with smart-casual attire.
      </p>
      <p>
        The silver dial acts as a neutral canvas, reflecting the colors around it. In warm light it takes on a creamy tone; in cool light it becomes crisp and sterile. The date window at 3 o'clock is discreet, blending into the minute track without disturbing the dial's symmetry.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="story-quote">
        "The Hamilton Jazzmaster H32505731 proves that a dress watch doesn't need complications to be compelling. Sometimes the most honest timepiece is the one that simply tells time well."
      </blockquote>

      <div class="story-specs">
        <h3>At a Glance: Hamilton Jazzmaster H32505731</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Movement:</strong> H-10 Automatic, 80h power reserve</li>
          <li><strong>Case:</strong> Stainless steel, 40mm</li>
          <li><strong>Crystal:</strong> Sapphire</li>
          <li><strong>Dial:</strong> Silver with applied indices</li>
          <li><strong>Strap:</strong> Black leather with deployant buckle</li>
          <li><strong>Water Resistance:</strong> 50m</li>
          <li><strong>Caseback:</strong> Sapphire exhibition</li>
          <li><strong>Price:</strong> $502.53</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="story-cta">
        <p>This piece and hundreds more are waiting to become part of your story.</p>
        <a href="/watches" class="btn">Explore the Collection</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .story-article { max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem; }
  .story-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .story-category { font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .story-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-meta-line { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .story-hero-img { margin: 0 -1.5rem 3rem; text-align: center; background: var(--color-border); padding: 2rem; }
  .story-hero-img img { max-width: 300px; height: auto; }
  .story-body { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--color-text); }
  .story-lede { font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); }
  .story-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .story-quote { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: #f5f0e8; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text); border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; }
  .story-specs { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: #faf8f5; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-specs h3 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-specs ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .story-specs li { padding: 0.4rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .story-specs li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .story-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-border)); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-cta p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .story-article { padding: 2rem 1rem; }
    .story-header h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  }
</style>
